commit.message:
igsc: bump version to 0.8.16

Update CHANGELOG.md

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>

igsc: cli: add delay between the update and get firmware version

Add delay between the update and get firmware version,
to be on the safe side.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: bump version to 0.8.15

Update CHANGELOG.md

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>

igsc: conan: use metee 3.2.4

Use MeTee with the fix for reconnect on error

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: wait for reset at the end of the update in cp mode

At the end of the update add a wait for the firmware reset
completion.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: wait for background operation to finish

Add a loop that waits for the firmware background operation to
finish at the end of the update

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: bump version to 0.8.14

Update CHANGELOG.md

Signed-off-by: Alexander Usyskin <alexander.usyskin@intel.com>

igsc: gitignore: add full VisualStudio ignore

Ignore VisualStudio temporary files.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Usyskin <alexander.usyskin@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: cli: do not use relative includes

Do not use up tree path includes, prefer to redefine the macro.

Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: cli: the global variables used only in one c file should be static

The log level variables should be static.

Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: move chunk_size declaration to its scope in gsc_update

In gsc_update, chunk_size variable is used only in the loop,
define it there.

Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: Windows: generate pdb in Release build

Generate pdb in Release Windows build.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Usyskin <alexander.usyskin@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: ut: update cmake for new cmocka packaging

Linux distro now comes with cmocka-config.cmake configuration,
support this setting in test cmake.

Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: bump version to 0.8.13

Update CHANGELOG.md

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: disconnect on failure in gsc_driver_init

Disconnect the device handler on failure of TeeConnect
in gsc_driver_init to close the device descriptor that was open
previously by TeeInit.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: ut: add mock to the new metee api

Add mock implementation to the new metee APIs:
TeeSetLogLevel and TeeGetLogLevel

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: set tee log level to quiet around firmware reset flow

Quiet the Tee library log level in runtime around firmware reset flow.
During the firmware reset the firmware is not responsive, which causes
several errors on metee/libmei levels.
The errors are actually expected and should not be shown to the user.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: suppress specific errors during firmware reset

Suppress error messages in time of firmware reset during firmware
update. Those error messages are expected and do not 'indicate error
condition.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: conan: use metee 3.2.3

Use MeTee with option to quiet libmei errors in run-time

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: set security policy for the project

Add SECURITY.md to the project.
Supported versions are 0.8.10 and newer.

Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: remove redundant assignments

Remove redundant assignments of metadata_start and metadata_end
as they were already assigned a few lines before.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: fix possible null pointer dereference

Fix possible null pointer dereference in debug print functions

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: bump version to 0.8.11

Update CHANGELOG.md

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: cli: add trace mode to cli

Add trace run mode to cli

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: cli: set libary log level in verbose mode

Set libary log level to 'DEBUG' in verbose mode

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: drop ifdef DEBUG around log prints

Drop ifdef DEBUG around log prints, the log level is
being controlled in run-time

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: implement log levels

Implement ERROR, DEBUG and TRACE log levels

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: fix debug messages that should have been printed as errors

Some debug messages that should have been printed in error level,
fix that.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: use %z for size_t printing

Change %l specifiers to %z for size_t printing.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>

igsc: lib: move received and sent data prints from debug to trace

Received and sent heci data is very long. We move the log prints from
debug to trace, to be able to separate the log levels.

Signed-off-by: Vitaly Lubart <vitaly.lubart@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Tomas Winkler <tomas.winkler@intel.com>
